<reference id="api_onvideostopped">
    <title><ph keyref="onVideoStopped"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">Occurs when the video view is destroyed.</ph></shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
   <keywords>
       <indexterm keyref="onVideoStopped" />
   </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody><section id="prototype">
        
        <p conref="../conref/conref_rtc_api.dita#apidef/onVideoStopped"/>
        </section>
        <section id="detailed_desc">
   
   <dl outputclass="deprecated">
       <dlentry >
  <dt>Deprecated:</dt>
  <dd>Deprecated as of v2.4.1. Please use <xref keyref="onLocalVideoStateChanged"/>(0) in the callback <apiname keyref="LOCAL_VIDEO_STREAM_STATE_STOPPED"/>instead.</dd>
       </dlentry>
   </dl>
   <p>Prompt that the video function has been stopped. The application can use this callback to change the configuration of the <parmname>view</parmname> (for example, displaying other pictures in the<parmname> view</parmname>) after the video stops playing.</p>
